# Windows PowerShell scripts: CRLF line endings. The files are committed with a
# UTF-8 BOM as part of their content — Windows PowerShell 5.1 otherwise decodes
# BOM-less files as Windows-1252 and corrupts non-ASCII characters inside string
# literals (which breaks parsing). Do not strip the BOM when editing.
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Unix shell scripts must keep LF, or shebangs break on Linux/macOS.
*.sh  text eol=lf

*.md   text
*.json text

*.png binary
